data.title: St Andrew's Church, East Heslerton, North Yorkshire
data.meta_description: A tall tower and wonderful views
data.text:
A tall tower and wonderful views

St Andrew's stands in a large peaceful churchyard at the southern end of the hamlet. With wonderful views over the surrounding countryside, this village church, completed in 1877, boasts a striking 32-metre spire.

The church is in the Transitional style, with an Italian feel. The exuberant Victorian interior - designed as a complete, unified scheme by G E Street - is particularly impressive.

Inside, the oak pews are set in an oak-boarded floor, and the stone pulpit is particularly fine.

Your support and generosity is what helps us keep the doors to these special places open.
